commitResults.messageBody:
In the previous format, there is no good way to definitively construct a
Task, the user could have used brackets and spaces etc. in the title.

The new format is:
* First line represents the type of Task
* Second line represents the title
* Third line, if there is any, represents the by (for Deadline) or at (for
Event)
* Use empty line to separate between Tasks

Using TaskMapper to handle the conversion between Task and its
String representation makes the code cleaner.

commitResults.messageBody:
Blue class has:
* deeply nested method
* magic literal
* dead code
* unnecessary class attributes
which negatively impacts the code quality.

Let's refactor them.

commitResults.messageTitle: Command class: refactor into Command enum
commitResults.messageBody:
Command class contains String constants for the commands. This reduces the flexibility of the
chatbot to specify which inputs match the commands.

Let's change the Command class into a Command enum, and pass the responsibility of matching the
user inputs to commands to the Parser class.

Letting the Parser class to handle the matching of inputs to commands is appropriate because it
has a getCommand method which is called by the Blue class to get the Command. The level of
abstraction is also consistent within the Parser class.

Improve code quality and fix saving bug
commitResults.messageBody:
Code quality:
* Delete dead code
* Use constants to replace methods for task representations - suggested by @xyliew25
* Replace String literals with constants

Save is not called anywhere, so the tasks are not saved every time after modifying task list.
Let's let the Blue class to be the intermediary between GUI and Storage.

Text-based UI is no longer needed. Let's remove the Ui class.
